statdata <- read.csv('../Gut_Microbiome_Data/gut_full.csv', check.names=F)
dfOR = data.frame(matrix(ncol = 0, nrow = 4))
dfOR_ci = data.frame(matrix(ncol = 0, nrow = 4))
#Summary Statistics of Cohort
#print(col)
pom <- polr(factor(bowel, ordered = TRUE) ~BMI_CALC + factor(sex) + age + eGFR, data=statdata, Hess=TRUE, control=list(maxit=300))
  
## store table
(ctable <- coef(summary(pom)))
                    Value  Std. Error     t value

#print(ctable)

## calculate and store p values
p <- pnorm(abs(ctable[, "t value"]), lower.tail = FALSE) * 2
#print(p)
## combined table
ctable <- cbind(ctable, "p value" = p)
ci <- confint(pom) # default method gives profiled CIs
Waiting for profiling to be done...
## OR and CI
dfOR_ci <- cbind(exp(cbind('variable' = coef(pom), ci)),dfOR_ci)
dfOR <- cbind('p value' = p[1:4],dfOR)

#P value dataframe for all variables
colnames(dfOR)[which((names(dfOR) == 'p value') | (names(dfOR) == '2.5 %') | (names(dfOR) == '97.5 %'))]   <- paste(c('p value','2.5 %', '97.5 %'),sep="-")

print(dfOR_ci)

#Depression data from health history data of Arivale
dep <- read.csv('../Survey_Data/depression.csv', check.names=F)
dfOR = data.frame(matrix(ncol = 0, nrow = 7))
dfOR_ci = data.frame(matrix(ncol = 0, nrow = 7))
dep <- dep[,2:ncol(dep)]
dep[dep == 'FALSE'] <- 0
dep[dep == 'TRUE'] <- 1
dep$bowel <- factor(dep$bowel) #factorize BMF
dep$sex <- factor(dep$sex) #factorize sex
dep <- within(dep, bowel <- relevel(bowel, ref = "High Normal")) #set the reference category as "High Normal" BMF

dep[,c(6:ncol(dep))][sapply(dep[,c(6:ncol(dep))], is.double)] <- lapply(dep[,c(6:ncol(dep))][sapply(dep[,c(6:ncol(dep))], is.double)], 
                                       as.factor)
my_names <- names(dep)[-which(colnames(dep) == 'bowel'| colnames(dep) == 'BMI_CALC' | colnames(dep) == 'sex' | colnames(dep) == 'age' | colnames(dep) == 'eGFR')]

i = 5
p = data.frame(matrix(ncol = 0, nrow = 7))
for(col in my_names){
  i = i + 1
  pom[[i-5]] <- glm(get(my_names[[i-5]]) ~ bowel + sex + age + BMI_CALC + eGFR, data = dep, family="binomial")
  print(summary(pom[[i-5]]))
  p[[i-5]] <- coef(summary(pom[[i-5]]))[2:8,4]
  p[[i-5]] <- p.adjust(p[[i-5]], method = "fdr", n = (length(dep) - 5))
  names(p)[i-5] <- paste0(my_names[[i-5]],sep="")
}

#Anxiety data from health history data of Arivale
anx <- read.csv('../Survey_Data/anxiety.csv', check.names=F)
dfOR = data.frame(matrix(ncol = 0, nrow = 7))

anx <- anx[,2:ncol(anx)]
anx[anx == 'FALSE'] <- 0
anx[anx == 'TRUE'] <- 1
anx$bowel <- factor(anx$bowel)
anx$sex <- factor(anx$sex)
anx <- within(anx, bowel <- relevel(bowel, ref = "High Normal"))

anx[,c(6:ncol(anx))][sapply(anx[,c(6:ncol(anx))], is.double)] <- lapply(anx[,c(6:ncol(anx))][sapply(anx[,c(6:ncol(anx))], is.double)], 
                                       as.factor)
my_names <- names(anx)[-which(colnames(anx) == 'bowel'| colnames(anx) == 'BMI_CALC' | colnames(anx) == 'sex' | colnames(anx) == 'age' | colnames(anx) == 'eGFR')]

i = 5
p = data.frame(matrix(ncol = 0, nrow = 7))
for(col in my_names){  
  i = i + 1
  pom[[i-5]] <- glm(get(my_names[[i-5]]) ~ bowel + sex + age + BMI_CALC + eGFR, data = anx, family="binomial")
  print(summary(pom[[i-5]]))
  p[[i-5]] <- coef(summary(pom[[i-5]]))[2:8,4]
  p[[i-5]] <- p.adjust(p[[i-5]], method = "fdr", n = (length(anx) - 5))
  names(p)[i-5] <- paste0(my_names[[i-5]],sep="")
}

#Linear model of PTR data:
ptr <- (read.csv(file = 'ptr_plot.csv'))
order <- c("Constipation", "Low Normal", "High Normal", "Diarrhea")

model <- lm(overall_means ~ bowel + eGFR + sex + age + BMI_CALC, data = ptr)
